definitions.definition: A mesh of string, cord or rope.
definitions.example: a hairnet; a mosquito net; a tennis net

definitions.definition: A device made from such mesh, used for catching fish, butterflies, etc.
A device made from such mesh, generally used for trapping something.
Anything that has the appearance of such a device.
(by extension) A trap.
definitions.example: caught in the prosecuting attorney's net

definitions.definition: (geometry) Of a polyhedron, any set of polygons joined edge to edge that, when folded along the edges between adjoining polygons so that the outer edges touch, form the polyhedron.
A system that interconnects a number of users, locations etc. allowing transport or communication between them.
definitions.example: (electronics) A conductor that interconnects two or more component terminals.

definitions.definition: (sports) A framework backed by a mesh, serving as the goal in hockey, soccer, lacrosse, etc.
definitions.example: The striker headed the ball into the net to make it 1-0.

definitions.definition: (sports, tennis) A mesh stretched to divide the court in tennis, badminton, volleyball, etc.
(tennis, by extension) The area of the court close to the net (mesh stretched to divide the court).
(electronics) A conductor that interconnects two or more component terminals.
(transitive) To catch by means of a net.
(transitive, figuratively) To catch in a trap, or by stratagem.
To enclose or cover with a net.
(transitive, soccer) To score (a goal).
definitions.example: Evans netted the winner in the 80th minute.

definitions.definition: (tennis) To hit the ball into the net.
To form a netting or network; to knit.
(obsolete) Good, desirable; clean, decent, clear.
Free from extraneous substances; pure; unadulterated; neat.
Remaining after expenses or deductions.
Final; end.
After expenses or deductions.
The amount remaining after expenses are deducted; profit.
